# Size & Density System Law

## Core Architecture

The Size System provides three global UI density presets. ALL layout dimensions, font sizes, spacing, and border radii MUST be derived from these presets via CSS variables. **Hardcoded pixel values for layout dimensions are FORBIDDEN.**

SSOT files:
- Presets: `src/constants/size.ts` (`SIZE_PRESETS`)
- Types: `src/types/systems/size.d.ts` (`SizeMode`, `SizePreset`, `SizeCssVars`)
- Engine: `src/utils/theme/sizeEngine.ts`
- Runtime store: `src/stores/modules/size.ts` (`useSizeStore`)

---

## The Three Density Presets

| Property | `compact` | `comfortable` (default) | `loose` |
|---|---|---|---|
| `fontSizeBase` | 14px | 16px | 18px |
| `spacingBase` | 4px | 4px | 4px |
| `radius` | 6px | 8px | 12px |
| `sidebarWidth` | 200px | 240px | 280px |
| `sidebarCollapsedWidth` | 56px | 60px | 80px |
| `headerHeight` | 48px | 60px | 66px |
| `breadcrumbHeight` | 28px | 32px | 36px |
| `footerHeight` | 28px | 32px | 38px |
| `tabsHeight` | 36px | 40px | 46px |

**FORBIDDEN**: Using these raw pixel numbers in any business code. They are engine internals.

---

## CSS Variable Pipeline (Two Paths)

### Path A — Static Ladder Variables (preset-driven, device-agnostic)

Generated by `generateSizeVars(preset)`, written by `applySizeTheme()`. Computed once per preset change:

| Variable | Formula | Example (comfortable) |
|---|---|---|
| `--spacing-unit` | `spacingBase` | `4px` |
| `--container-padding` | `spacingBase × 5` | `20px` |
| `--spacing-xs` | `spacingBase × 1` | `4px` |
| `--spacing-sm` | `spacingBase × 2` | `8px` |
| `--spacing-md` | `spacingBase × 4` | `16px` |
| `--spacing-lg` | `spacingBase × 6` | `24px` |
| `--spacing-xl` | `spacingBase × 8` | `32px` |
| `--radius-xs` | `radius × 0.25` | `2px` |
| `--radius-sm` | `radius × 0.5` | `4px` |
| `--radius-md` | `radius × 1` | `8px` |
| `--radius-lg` | `radius × 1.5` | `12px` |
| `--transition-xs` | fixed `180ms` | `180ms` |
| `--transition-sm` | fixed `280ms` | `280ms` |
| `--transition-md` | fixed `320ms` | `320ms` |

Full scale runs `xs / sm / md / lg / xl / 2xl / 3xl / 4xl / 5xl` for spacing, radius, and transition.

### Path B — Responsive Variables (device + breakpoint + preset)

Generated by `decideRootFontSize(ctx)` + `decideLayoutDimensions(ctx)`, written by `applyRuntimeSizeUpdate()`. Recalculate on every resize event:

**Font size** (`--font-size-root`, `--font-size-xs` through `--font-size-5xl`):
- Computed as `fontSizeBase × FONT_SCALE_RATIO[scaleKey]`
- `scaleKey` resolved from `{deviceType, breakpoint}` inside `decideRootFontSize()`

**Layout dimensions** — PC only scales by breakpoint via `LAYOUT_SCALE_RATIOS`; Mobile/Tablet always use ratio = 1:

| Breakpoint | Scale ratio | `--sidebar-width` (comfortable) |
|---|---|---|
| xs, sm, md, lg | ×1.00 | 240px |
| xl | ×1.05 | 252px |
| 2xl | ×1.10 | 264px |
| 3xl | ×1.15 | 276px |
| 4xl | ×1.20 | 288px |
| 5xl | ×1.25 | 300px |

