## UnoCSS Class → CSS Variable Mapping

### Content-level tokens (spacing, typography, radius, transition)

| UnoCSS class | CSS variable | Example value (comfortable) |
|---|---|---|
| `p-xs` / `gap-xs` | `--spacing-xs` | `4px` |
| `p-sm` / `gap-sm` | `--spacing-sm` | `8px` |
| `p-md` / `gap-md` | `--spacing-md` | `16px` |
| `p-lg` / `gap-lg` | `--spacing-lg` | `24px` |
| `text-xs` | `--font-size-xs` | `≈12px` |
| `text-sm` | `--font-size-sm` | `≈14px` |
| `text-base` | `--font-size-md` | `≈16px` |
| `text-lg` | `--font-size-lg` | `≈18px` |
| `rounded-sm` | `--radius-sm` | `4px` |
| `rounded-md` | `--radius-md` | `8px` |
| `rounded-lg` | `--radius-lg` | `12px` |
| `rounded-full` | `--radius-5xl` | `999px` (capsule) |
| `duration-xs` | `--transition-xs` | `180ms` |
| `duration-sm` | `--transition-sm` | `280ms` |
| `duration-md` | `--transition-md` | `320ms` |

### Shell-level tokens (layout dimensions — admin layout ONLY)

| UnoCSS class | CSS variable |
|---|---|
| `w-sidebarWidth` | `--sidebar-width` |
| `w-sidebarCollapsedWidth` | `--sidebar-collapsed-width` |
| `h-headerHeight` | `--header-height` |
| `h-breadcrumbHeight` | `--breadcrumb-height` |
| `h-footerHeight` | `--footer-height` |
| `h-tabsHeight` | `--tabs-height` |

---

## Dynamic Content Height Pattern

Content area height is NOT a fixed CSS variable — it depends on active layout mode. Compute explicitly:

```html
<!-- With tabs bar visible -->
<div class="col-fill"
  style="height: calc(100vh - var(--header-height) - var(--footer-height) - var(--tabs-height))">
```

```html
<!-- Without tabs bar -->
<div class="col-fill"
  style="height: calc(100vh - var(--header-height) - var(--footer-height))">
```

---

## Runtime API

```typescript
import { useSizeStore } from '@/stores/modules/size'

const sizeStore = useSizeStore()

// Switch global density mode (triggers full CSS var re-injection)
sizeStore.setSize('compact')     // fontSizeBase 14, sidebarWidth 200
sizeStore.setSize('comfortable') // default — fontSizeBase 16, sidebarWidth 240
sizeStore.setSize('loose')       // fontSizeBase 18, sidebarWidth 280

// Read current mode
const currentMode: SizeMode = sizeStore.sizeName
```

---

## Absolute Prohibitions

| FORBIDDEN | CORRECT |
|---|---|
| `width: 200px` (sidebarWidth) | `w-sidebarWidth` |
| `height: 60px` (headerHeight) | `h-headerHeight` |
| `font-size: 16px` | `text-base` |
| `padding: 16px` | `p-md` |
| `border-radius: 8px` | `rounded-md` |
| `transition-duration: 300ms` | `duration-md` |
| `duration-300`, `duration-200` (raw Tailwind) | `duration-sm`, `duration-md` |
| `useSizeStore().setSize('spacious')` | `'spacious'` is NOT a valid `SizeMode` |
| Importing `SIZE_PRESETS` in view/component files | Use CSS vars via Uno classes |

```typescript
// ❌ FORBIDDEN: hardcoding preset values
const SIDEBAR_WIDTH = 240
element.style.width = `${SIDEBAR_WIDTH}px`

// ✅ REQUIRED: CSS variable via Uno class
// <div class="w-sidebarWidth"> — maps to var(--sidebar-width)
```
